                <h1>"The History of Nike Dunks: Debut and Legacy"</h1>
                <p>Nike Dunks first debuted in 1985 as a basketball shoe aimed at college teams. Originally released as the Dunk High, the sneaker quickly gained traction in the fashion world, influencing streetwear culture. Over the years, various iterations and collaborations have solidified its iconic status among sneaker enthusiasts.</p>
